description.narrative: 2.2 National and subnational actors have increased capacity to deliver child health and nurturing care services to very young children within primary health care., which contributes to Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Disaster Risk Reduction, Early Childhood Development, Immunization, Immunization (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025, girls and boys and their caregivers, especially vulnerable, enhance equitable, evidence-based, quality and gender- sensitive neonatal, child and adolescent health, nutrition, and development interventions for surviving and thriving
